The paper discusses a machine learning technique (multi-task learning) and proposes a framework for distributed and asynchronous optimization. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) categories. Additionally, the paper mentions healthcare and predictive modeling, which are common applications of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Computer Vision (cs.CV). Finally, the paper discusses regularized MTL formulations, which may fall under the Systems and Control (cs.SY) category.
